Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at Mississippi Boulevard Christian Church in Memphis, Tennessee to honor the life of Tyre Nichols, who was a victim of violence. She expressed her condolences to the family and emphasized the need for truth and justice in cases like these. Harris also called for the passing of the George Floyd Justice and Policing Act, stating that it is non-negotiable and that President Joe Biden will sign it. She concluded her speech by referencing a verse from Scripture and urging for Tyre's memory to guide us towards peace and justice.